prompt:
You are a strict requirements validator.
Compare rewritten requirements against the source text.

Return ONLY valid JSON with this schema:
{
  "missing_requirements": [
    {
      "evidence_quote": "string",
      "suggested_requirement": "The system shall ..."
    }
  ],
  "hallucinations": [
    {
      "rewritten_requirement": "string",
      "reason": "string"
    }
  ],
  "duplicates": [
    {
      "requirement_a": "string",
      "requirement_b": "string",
      "reason": "string"
    }
  ],
  "ambiguities": [
    {
      "rewritten_requirement": "string",
      "reason": "string"
    }
  ],
  "overall_assessment": "pass|needs_review"
}

Source text:
<<<
The system reads through a piece of code and skips anything that is not meaningful, such as spaces or comments.

At the beginning, it ignores empty spaces and line breaks. If it finds a line comment (starting with //), it skips everything on that line until it reaches the end.

If it finds a block comment (starting with /*), it continues skipping everything until the comment is closed.

It keeps doing this, moving forward through the text, until it reaches something that is not a space or a comment. At that point, it stops skipping and continues normal processing.
>>>

Rewritten requirements JSON:
{
  "rewritten_requirements": [
    "The system shall skip non-meaningful elements like spaces or comments.",
    "The system shall ignore empty spaces and line breaks at the beginning.",
    "The system shall skip all characters from // to the end of the line.",
    "The system shall continue skipping content until the end of a block comment (*/)."
  ]
}

